obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (29993)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00062_193726_1523351646990&sectionId=29993&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00062_193726_1523351646990
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Muslim Personal Law (Shariat)`
  line `Application Act, 1937.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1 [^2***]. ^3*** ^4`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 48 of 1959, s. 3 and the First Schedule for "except the territories which, immediately before the 1st November,`
  line `1956, were comprised in Part B States" (w.e.f. 1-2-1960).`
  line
  line `2. The words "excluding the North-West Frontier Province" omitted by the Indian Independence (Adaptation of Central Acts and`
  line `Ordinances) Order, 1948.`
  line
  line `3. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
  line
  line `4. In its application to Pondicherry. In section 1, after sub-section (2), the following shall be inserted--`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this act shall apply to the Renoncants of the Union territory of`
  line `Pondicherry.-- Vide Act 26 of 1968.)`
  line
  line `The Act has been extended to Dadra and Nagar Haveli by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and Sch. I and to the whole of the Union`
  line `territory of Lakshadweep by Reg. 8 of 1965, s. 3 and Sch.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (29994)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Application of Personal Law to Muslims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00062_193726_1523351646990&sectionId=29994&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00062_193726_1523351646990
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any custom or usage to the contrary,`
  line `in all questions (save questions relating to agricultural land) regarding intestate succession, special`
  line `property of females, including personal properly inherited or obtained under contract or gift or any other`
  line `provision of Personal Law. marriage, dissolution of marriage, including talaq, ila, zihar, lian, khula and`
  line `mubaraat, maintenance, dower, guardianship, gifts, trusts and trust properties, and wakfs (other than`
  line `charities and charitable institutions and charitable and religious endowments) the rule of decision in cases`
  line `where the parties are Muslims shall be the Muslim Personal Law (Shariat).`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Kerala.
  line
  line `Substitution of a new section for section 2, Central Act 26 of 1937.--For section 2 of the said Act,`
  line `the following section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `“2. Application of personal law to Muslims.--Notwithstanding any custom or usage to the`
  line `contrary, in all questions regarding intestate succession, special property of females including personal`
  line `property inherited or obtained under contract or gift or any other provision of personal laws, marriage,`
  line `dissolution of marriage, including talaq, ila, zihar, lian, khula and mubaraat, maintenance, dower,`
  line `guardianship, gifts, trusts and trust properties and wakfs (other than charities and charitable institutions`
  line `and charitable and religious endowments), the rules of decision in cases where the parties are Muslims,`
  line `shall be the Muslim Personal Law (Shariat).”`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 42 of 1963, s. 3.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (29995)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to make a declaration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00062_193726_1523351646990&sectionId=29995&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00062_193726_1523351646990
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who satisfies the prescribed authority--`
  line
  line `(a) that he is a Muslim, and`
  line
  line `(b) that he is competent to contract within the meaning of section 11 of the Indian Contract`
  line `Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), and`
  line
  line `(c) that he is a resident of ^1[the territories to which this Act extends],`
  line
  line `may by declaration in the prescribed form and filed before the prescribed authority declare that he desires`
  line `to obtain the benefit of ^2[the provisions of this section], and thereafter the provisions of section 2 shall`
  line `apply to the declarant and all his minor children and their descendants as if in addition to the matters`
  line `enumerated therein adoption, wills and legacies were also specified.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the prescribed authority refuses to accept a declaration under sub-section (1), the person`
  line `desiring to make the same may appeal to such office as the State Government may, by general or special`
  line `order, appoint in this behalf, and such officer may, if he is satisfied that the appellant is entitled to make`
  line `the declaration, order the prescribed authority to accept the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for "a Part A State or a Part C State".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 1943, s. 2, for "this Act" (w.e.f. 7-4-1943).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (29996)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Rule-making power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00062_193726_1523351646990&sectionId=29996&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00062_193726_1523351646990
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may make rules to carry into effect the purposes`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for prescribing the authority before whom and the form in which declaration under this Act`
  line `shall be made;`
  line
  line `(b) for prescribing the fees to be paid for the filing of declarations and for the attendance at`
  line `private residences of any person in the discharge of his duties under this Act; and for prescribing the`
  line `times at which such fees shall be payable and the manner in which they shall be levied.`
  line
  line `(3) Rules made under the provisions of this section shall be published, in the Official Gazette and`
  line `shall thereupon have effect as if enacted in this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as it is made,`
  line `before the State Legislature.]`
